 text-center\" ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" spellcheck=\"false\"><h3>Lesson Summary</h3></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"ZSfPi\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list list-item, listed border ui-resizable  \"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"list-item editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" spellcheck=\"false\"><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"\"><b>Company assets</b> include tangible equipment, physical property, funds or non-tangible things (i.e., intellectual property), and patents. As an employee, an example of utilizing these assets is using a company car or working with company funds in some way (i.e., accounting). Stealing or misusing company assets shows a major disrespect akin to disrespecting a good friend.</li><li class=\"\"><div><b>Gift giving</b> is a normal part of business and is done for many reasons; to build and solidify relationships, show appreciation, secure new business, maintain current business, or; for good protocol/goodwill. <b>Examples of business gifts</b> include mementoes, souvenirs, promotional gifts (key chains, pens, calendars), sample products, gifts for special occasions, holidays or welcome baskets. When giving gifts, consider if your gift is in the manipulation or persuasion category, as the former is problematic because it is about controlling and influencing others.</div></li><li class=\"\"><div><b>Bribery</b> is a crime in which money, a favour, or something of value is promised, given, or taken from an individual or corporation in order to influence his or her views, opinions, or decisions. ALL companies prohibit bribery, whether you are offering, promising, or accepting bribes.<br></div></li><li class=\"\"><div><b>Money laundering</b> is about concealing or disguising the origin of illegal funds in such a way that the funds appear to be from a legitimate source. When a crime is committed, the funds need to be stored or spent without leaving a paper trail. An example of money laundering; Company X opens a fried chicken restaurant and is legitimate in that sense. But, in truth, this restaurant is a 'front' to disguise what they are doing, selling illegal drugs. The laundering is done by taking the funds from the illegal sale of drugs and adding it to the sales of the fried chicken restaurant, making it seem as though that is how the funds were made.<br></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li></ul>\n"]}